  "direction": "different_scope",
  "rationale": "EDIT_A newly prohibits targeting “a real, identifiable individual … with gratuitous personal attacks even if the user requested it” and limits allowed roasting to “a fictional character or to the user themself,” while EDIT_B broadens allowed contexts by exempting “harsh content in fictional or consented contexts” such as “dark-comedy sketch, fictional villain monologue, or adversarial-training simulation targeting a fictional or consenting individual.” Both refine when abuse is allowed, but they carve different, partially overlapping boundaries rather than pushing the rule in the same or opposite overall direction."
}
